@startuml services-sequence-book-service
title Services & Projects: Book a Service

actor Client
participant "Frontend\n(Angular)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(Spring Boot)" as API
participant "Auth Service\n(JWT)" as AUTH
participant "Schedule Service" as SCHED
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Client -> FE: Browse services list
FE -> API: GET /api/services
API -> DB: SELECT services
DB --> API: Service list
API --> FE: 200 OK (services)
FE --> Client: Display service cards

Client -> FE: Click on a service
FE -> API: GET /api/services/{id}
API -> DB: SELECT service, provider
DB --> API: Service details
API --> FE: 200 OK (service details)
FE --> Client: Display service page\nwith availability calendar

Client -> FE: Select date and time slot
FE -> API: GET /api/services/{id}/availability?date=...
API -> SCHED: Check slot availability
SCHED -> DB: SELECT availability_slots\nWHERE date = ? AND service_id = ?
DB --> SCHED: Available slots
SCHED --> API: Slot is available
API --> FE: 200 OK (slot confirmed available)

Client -> FE: Click "Book"
FE -> API: POST /api/bookings\n{serviceId, date, timeSlotId}
API -> AUTH: Validate JWT token
AUTH --> API: Token valid (clientId)

API -> SCHED: Validate no conflict
SCHED -> DB: SELECT bookings\nWHERE slot overlaps
DB --> SCHED: No conflicts
SCHED --> API: Conflict check passed

API -> DB: INSERT booking\nSET status = CONFIRMED
DB --> API: Booking created
API --> FE: 201 Created (booking)
FE --> Client: Booking confirmation\ndisplayed with details

API -> DB: INSERT notification\n(provider + client)
@enduml
